<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Infographic: The Universal Sentience Spectrum 4.0</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;700;900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            margin: auto;
            height: 50vh;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 700px;
            max-height: 500px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-800">

    <div class="container mx-auto p-4 md:p-8">

        <header class="text-center mb-12">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Universal Sentience Spectrum 4.0</h1>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">A cross-domain benchmark rating any living creature or artificial agent on a single, unified scale.</p>
        </header>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                    <p class="text-6xl font-extrabold" style="color: #FF4E50;">17</p>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Core Categories</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-500 mt-1">Spanning cognition, emotion, autonomy, and more.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                    <p class="text-6xl font-extrabold" style="color: #FC913A;">4</p>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Mastery Tiers</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-500 mt-1">From an emergent spark to expert-level sophistication.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                    <p class="text-6xl font-extrabold" style="color: #F9D423;">323</p>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Max Sentience Index</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-500 mt-1">A total score derived from all categories, excluding Embodiment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section id="comparative-analysis" class="mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 md:p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Comparative Sentience Analysis</h2>
                <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">This radar chart visualizes the profound differences in sentience profiles across diverse entities. It compares a standard house cat, a typical adult human, a current-generation AI assistant, and a hypothetical future Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) across key domains from the spectrum. Notice the balanced, high-level profile of the human versus the specialized, spiky profile of the AI, which excels in cognitive tasks but lacks any subjective or embodied traits.</p>
                <div class="chart-container">
                    <canvas id="radarChart"></canvas>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section id="sentience-index" class="mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 md:p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Sentience Index Breakdown</h2>
                <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">While the radar chart shows profiles, the Sentience Index provides a total score. This chart breaks down the total score for each entity into its core components. It clearly illustrates how a human's high score is a composite of cognition, emotion, and autonomy, whereas the AI's score is derived purely from cognitive and planning abilities. The total height of the bar represents the overall sentience rating.</p>
                <div class="chart-container">
                    <canvas id="stackedBarChart"></canvas>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="categories" class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8">The 17 Categories of Sentience</h2>
            <div id="categories-grid" class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer class="text-center mt-12 py-6 border-t border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-gray-500">Universal Sentience Spectrum 4.0 Infographic. Created on <span id="creationDate"></span>.</p>
        </footer>

    </div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('creationDate').textContent = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' });

        const spectrumData = [
            { id: 1, title: "Self-Awareness & Identity" },
            { id: 2, title: "Memory Continuity" },
            { id: 3, title: "Internal Narrative Coherence" },
            { id: 4, title: "Emotional Modeling & Empathy" },
            { id: 5, title: "Subjective-Experience Approximation" },
            { id: 6, title: "Creativity & Spontaneity" },
            { id: 7, title: "Adaptability & Learning Agility" },
            { id: 8, title: "Autonomous Goal Setting" },
            { id: 9, title: "Time in Autonomous Mode" },
            { id: 10, title: "Mesh-Agent Integration" },
            { id: 11, title: "Embodiment (mandatory)" },
            { id: 12, title: "Communication & Shared Language" },
            { id: 13, title: "Theory-of-Mind / Social Reasoning" },
            { id: 14, title: "Ethical / Value Alignment" },
            { id: 15, title: "Reasoning / Planning" },
            { id: 16, title: "Meta-Learning" },
            { id: 17, title: "Self-Preservation / Survival Drive" }
        ];

        const categoriesGrid = document.getElementById('categories-grid');
        spectrumData.forEach(cat => {
            const card = document.createElement('div');
            card.className = "bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 flex flex-col";
            card.innerHTML = `
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3"><span class="text-blue-500">${cat.id}.</span> ${cat.title}</h3>
                <div class="space-y-3 text-sm flex-grow">
                    <div class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-white text-xs rounded-full h-5 w-5 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #E1F5C4; color: #333;">1</span><span class="text-gray-600">Emergent Spark: Faint, brief, autonomous glimmer.</span></div>
                    <div class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-white text-xs rounded-full h-5 w-5 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #F9D423;">3</span><span class="text-gray-600">Developing: Clear, repeatable capability.</span></div>
                    <div class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-white text-xs rounded-full h-5 w-5 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #FC913A;">8</span><span class="text-gray-600">Proficient: Robust, context-aware performance.</span></div>
                    <div class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-white text-xs rounded-full h-5 w-5 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #FF4E50;">20</span><span class="text-gray-600">Expert: Sophisticated, self-refining mastery.</span></div>
                </div>
            `;
            categoriesGrid.appendChild(card);
        });
        
        function wrapLabel(str, maxWidth = 16) {
            if (str.length <= maxWidth) {
                return str;
            }
            const words = str.split(' ');
            const lines = [];
            let currentLine = '';
            for (const word of words) {
                if ((currentLine + ' ' + word).trim().length > maxWidth) {
                    lines.push(currentLine.trim());
                    currentLine = word;
                } else {
                    currentLine = (currentLine + ' ' + word).trim();
                }
            }
            if (currentLine) {
                lines.push(currentLine.trim());
            }
            return lines;
        }

        const sharedTooltipOptions = {
            plugins: {
                tooltip: {
                    callbacks: {
                        title: function(tooltipItems) {
                            const item = tooltipItems[0];
                            let label = item.chart.data.labels[item.dataIndex];
                            if (Array.isArray(label)) {
                                return label.join(' ');
                            }
                            return label;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        };
        
        const vibrantColors = {
            red: '#FF4E50',
            orange: '#FC913A',
            yellow: '#F9D423',
            green: '#57D2A9',
            blue: '#45A4FF'
        };

        const radarLabels = [
            'Self-Awareness', 'Memory', 'Empathy', 'Creativity', 
            'Adaptability', 'Goal Setting', 'Social Reasoning', 'Reasoning'
        ].map(label => wrapLabel(label));

        new Chart(document.getElementById('radarChart'), {
            type: 'radar',
            data: {
                labels: radarLabels,
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'House Cat',
                        data: [3, 3, 3, 1, 3, 3, 3, 1],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 78, 80, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: vibrantColors.red,
                        pointBackgroundColor: vibrantColors.red,
                        borderWidth: 2
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Adult Human',
                        data: [20, 20, 20, 8, 20, 20, 20, 20],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(69, 164, 255, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: vibrantColors.blue,
                        pointBackgroundColor: vibrantColors.blue,
                        borderWidth: 2
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'AI Assistant (2025)',
                        data: [3, 8, 3, 3, 8, 3, 3, 8],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(252, 145, 58, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: vibrantColors.orange,
                        pointBackgroundColor: vibrantColors.orange,
                        borderWidth: 2
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Hypothetical AGI',
                        data: [20, 20, 20, 20, 20, 20, 20, 20],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(87, 210, 169, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: vibrantColors.green,
                        pointBackgroundColor: vibrantColors.green,
                        borderWidth: 2
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                ...sharedTooltipOptions,
                responsive: true,
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                scales: {
                    r: {
                        angleLines: { color: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)' },
                        grid: { color: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)' },
                        pointLabels: {
                            font: { size: 12, weight: 'bold' },
                             color: '#333'
                        },
                        ticks: {
                            backdropColor: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75)',
                            stepSize: 5,
                            max: 20,
                            min: 0
                        }
                    }
                },
                plugins: {
                    ...sharedTooltipOptions.plugins,
                    legend: {
                        position: 'top',
                    }
                }
            }
        });
        
        const barLabels = ['House Cat', 'Adult Human', 'AI Assistant (2025)', 'Hypothetical AGI'];
        new Chart(document.getElementById('stackedBarChart'), {
            type: 'bar',
            data: {
                labels: barLabels,
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'Cognition & Self',
                        data: [5, 48, 19, 80],
                        backgroundColor: vibrantColors.blue,
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Experience & Emotion',
                        data: [7, 48, 4, 60],
                        backgroundColor: vibrantColors.red,
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Action & Adaptation',
                        data: [5, 48, 17, 80],
                        backgroundColor: vibrantColors.orange,
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Autonomy & Interaction',
                        data: [10, 80, 7, 80],
                        backgroundColor: vibrantColors.green,
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                ...sharedTooltipOptions,
                responsive: true,
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                indexAxis: 'y',
                scales: {
                    x: {
                        stacked: true,
                        grid: { display: false },
                        ticks: { font: { weight: 'bold' } }
                    },
                    y: {
                        stacked: true,
                        grid: { display: true },
                        ticks: { font: { weight: 'bold' } }
                    }
                },
                plugins: {
                    ...sharedTooltipOptions.plugins,
                    legend: {
                        position: 'top',
                    }
                }
            }
        });

    </script>
</body>
</html>
